        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You are given two non-negative integers num1 and num2. In one operation, if num1 >= num2, you must
                subtract
                num2 from num1, otherwise subtract num1 from num2. Return the number of operations required to make
                either
                num1 = 0 or num2 = 0.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: num1 = 2, num2 = 3 → Output: 3. Operation 1: num1 = 2, num2 = 3. Since num2 > num1, subtract num1
                from num2: num2 = 1. Operation 2: num1 = 2, num2 = 1. Since num1 > num2, subtract num2 from num1: num1 =
                1.
                Operation 3: num1 = 1, num2 = 1. Since num1 = num2, subtract num2 from num1: num1 = 0. Total = 3
                operations.
                Input: num1 = 10, num2 = 10 → Output: 1. Subtract num2 from num1 to get num1 = 0. Total = 1 operation.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int countOperations(int num1, int num2) {
        int cnt = 0;
        while (num1 != 0 &amp;&amp; num2 != 0)
        {
            if (num1 &gt;= num2)
            {
                cnt += num1 / num2;
                num1 %= num2;
            }
            else if (num2 &gt; num1)
            {
                cnt += num2 / num1;
                num2 %= num1;
            }
        }
        return cnt;
    }
};</code></pre>
